      "id": 100,
      "title": "🌐 HTTP Overview",
      "type": "row"
    },
    {
      "title": "Request Rate (req/s)",
      "description": "Total HTTP requests per second across all endpoints.\n\nThis is the primary indicator of traffic volume. Sudden spikes may indicate a viral link or an attack. Drops may indicate DNS issues or upstream failures.\n\nQuery: sum of rate() over all labels gives total throughput.",
      "type": "timeseries",
      "gridPos": {
        "h": 8,
        "w": 12,
        "x": 0,
        "y": 1
      },
      "id": 1,
      "datasource": {
        "type": "prometheus",
        "uid": "PBFA97CFB590B2093"
      },
      "fieldConfig": {
        "defaults": {
          "color": {
            "mode": "palette-classic"
          },
          "custom": {
            "axisBorderShow": false,
            "axisLabel": "req/s",
            "drawStyle": "line",
            "fillOpacity": 20,
            "gradientMode": "scheme",
            "lineInterpolation": "smooth",
            "lineWidth": 2,
            "pointSize": 5,
            "showPoints": "auto",
            "spanNulls": false,
            "stacking": {
              "group": "A",
              "mode": "none"
            }
          },
          "unit": "reqps"
        },
        "overrides": []
      },
      "options": {
        "legend": {
          "calcs": [
            "mean",
            "max"
          ],
          "displayMode": "table",
          "placement": "bottom"
        },
        "tooltip": {
          "mode": "multi",
          "sort": "desc"
        }
      },
      "targets": [
        {
          "expr": "sum by (path) (rate(urlshortener_http_requests_total[5m]))",
          "legendFormat": "{{path}}",
          "refId": "A"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "title": "Request Latency (p50 / p95 / p99)",
      "description": "Response time percentiles across all endpoints.\n\np50 = median (half of requests are faster)\np95 = 95th percentile (only 5% of requests are slower)\np99 = 99th percentile (only 1% are slower)\n\nFor a URL shortener, redirect (/:code) should be < 50ms at p95 when cache is warm. If p99 spikes but p50 stays low, you have a 'long tail' problem — most requests are fast but some are very slow.",
      "type": "timeseries",
      "gridPos": {
        "h": 8,
        "w": 12,
        "x": 12,
        "y": 1
      },
      "id": 2,
      "datasource": {
        "type": "prometheus",
        "uid": "PBFA97CFB590B2093"
      },
      "fieldConfig": {
        "defaults": {
          "color": {
            "mode": "palette-classic"
          },
          "custom": {
            "axisBorderShow": false,
            "axisLabel": "",
            "drawStyle": "line",
            "fillOpacity": 10,
            "lineInterpolation": "smooth",
            "lineWidth": 2,
            "pointSize": 5,
            "showPoints": "auto",
            "spanNulls": false
          },
          "unit": "s"
        },
        "overrides": []
      },
      "options": {
        "legend": {
          "calcs": [
            "mean",
            "max"
          ],
          "displayMode": "table",
          "placement": "bottom"
        },
        "tooltip": {
          "mode": "multi",
          "sort": "desc"
        }
      },
      "targets": [
        {
          "expr": "histogram_quantile(0.50, sum by (le) (rate(urlshortener_http_request_duration_seconds_bucket[5m])))",
          "legendFormat": "p50",
          "refId": "A"
        },
        {
          "expr": "histogram_quantile(0.95, sum by (le) (rate(urlshortener_http_request_duration_seconds_bucket[5m])))",
          "legendFormat": "p95",
          "refId": "B"
        },
        {
          "expr": "histogram_quantile(0.99, sum by (le) (rate(urlshortener_http_request_duration_seconds_bucket[5m])))",
          "legendFormat": "p99",
          "refId": "C"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "title": "Requests In Flight",
      "description": "Number of HTTP requests being processed at this moment.\n\nThis gauge shows concurrent load. If this number keeps climbing without dropping, requests are getting stuck (blocked on DB, deadlock, etc). Normal pattern: fluctuates around a low number, spikes briefly during traffic bursts.",
      "type": "timeseries",
      "gridPos": {
        "h": 8,
        "w": 8,
        "x": 0,
        "y": 9
      },
      "id": 3,
      "datasource": {
        "type": "prometheus",
        "uid": "PBFA97CFB590B2093"
      },
      "fieldConfig": {
        "defaults": {
          "color": {
            "fixedColor": "orange",
            "mode": "fixed"
          },
          "custom": {
            "axisBorderShow": false,
            "drawStyle": "line",
            "fillOpacity": 30,
            "lineInterpolation": "smooth",
            "lineWidth": 2
          },
          "unit": "none",
          "min": 0
        },
        "overrides": []
      },
      "options": {
        "legend": {
          "displayMode": "hidden"
        },
        "tooltip": {
          "mode": "single"
        }
      },
      "targets": [
        {
          "expr": "urlshortener_http_requests_in_flight",
          "legendFormat": "in-flight",
          "refId": "A"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "title": "Error Rate by Status Code",
      "description": "HTTP error responses per second, grouped by status code.\n\nFilters for 4xx and 5xx responses only. A spike in 4xx usually means bad client input or expired URLs. A spike in 5xx means something is broken server-side — DB down, panic recovery, etc.",
      "type": "timeseries",
      "gridPos": {
        "h": 8,
        "w": 8,
        "x": 8,
        "y": 9
      },
      "id": 4,
      "datasource": {
        "type": "prometheus",
        "uid": "PBFA97CFB590B2093"
      },
      "fieldConfig": {
        "defaults": {
          "color": {
            "mode": "palette-classic"
          },
          "custom": {
            "axisBorderShow": false,
            "drawStyle": "bars",
            "fillOpacity": 80,
            "lineWidth": 1,
            "stacking": {
              "group": "A",
              "mode": "normal"
            }
          },
          "unit": "reqps"
        },
        "overrides": []
      },
      "options": {
        "legend": {
          "calcs": [
            "sum"
          ],
          "displayMode": "table",
          "placement": "bottom"
        },
        "tooltip": {
          "mode": "multi",
          "sort": "desc"
        }
      },
      "targets": [
        {
          "expr": "sum by (status) (rate(urlshortener_http_requests_total{status=~\"4..|5..\"}[5m]))",
          "legendFormat": "HTTP {{status}}",
          "refId": "A"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "title": "Latency per Endpoint (p95)",
      "description": "95th percentile latency broken down by route.\n\nThis tells you which endpoints are slowest. The redirect endpoint (/:code) should be the fastest since it's the hot path. If /api/v1/shorten is slow, check DB write performance. If /me/urls is slow, check pagination queries.",
      "type": "timeseries",
      "gridPos": {
        "h": 8,
        "w": 8,
        "x": 16,
        "y": 9
      },
      "id": 5,
      "datasource": {
        "type": "prometheus",
        "uid": "PBFA97CFB590B2093"
      },
      "fieldConfig": {
        "defaults": {
          "color": {
            "mode": "palette-classic"
          },
          "custom": {
            "axisBorderShow": false,
            "drawStyle": "line",
            "fillOpacity": 10,
            "lineInterpolation": "smooth",
            "lineWidth": 2
          },
          "unit": "s"
        },
        "overrides": []
      },
      "options": {
        "legend": {
          "calcs": [
            "mean",
            "max"
          ],
          "displayMode": "table",
          "placement": "bottom"
        },
        "tooltip": {
          "mode": "multi",
          "sort": "desc"
        }
      },
      "targets": [
        {
          "expr": "histogram_quantile(0.95, sum by (le, path) (rate(urlshortener_http_request_duration_seconds_bucket{path!=\"\"}[5m])))",
          "legendFormat": "{{path}}",
          "refId": "A"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "collapsed": false,
      "gridPos": {
        "h": 1,
        "w": 24,
        "x": 0,
        "y": 17
      },
      "id": 200,
      "title": "📊 Cache Performance",
      "type": "row"
    },
    {
      "title": "Cache Hit Ratio (%)",
      "description": "Percentage of cache lookups that found the URL in Redis.\n\nThis is the single most important metric for redirect performance. Target: > 80% in production with warm cache.\n\nFormula: hits / (hits + misses) × 100\n\nIf this drops suddenly, possible causes:\n- Redis restarted (cache cold)\n- TTL too short\n- Traffic pattern changed (many new/unique URLs)\n- Redis memory full, evicting keys",
      "type": "gauge",
      "gridPos": {
        "h": 8,
        "w": 6,
        "x": 0,
        "y": 18
      },
      "id": 6,
      "datasource": {
        "type": "prometheus",
        "uid": "PBFA97CFB590B2093"
      },
      "fieldConfig": {
        "defaults": {
          "color": {
            "mode": "thresholds"
          },
          "thresholds": {
            "mode": "absolute",
            "steps": [
              {
                "color": "red",
                "value": null
              },
              {
                "color": "yellow",
                "value": 50
              },
              {
                "color": "green",
                "value": 80
              }
            ]
          },
          "unit": "percent",
          "min": 0,
          "max": 100
        },
        "overrides": []
      },
      "options": {
        "reduceOptions": {
          "calcs": [
            "lastNotNull"
          ]
        },
        "showThresholdLabels": false,
        "showThresholdMarkers": true
      },
      "targets": [
        {
          "expr": "rate(urlshortener_cache_requests_total{result=\"hit\"}[5m]) / (rate(urlshortener_cache_requests_total{result=\"hit\"}[5m]) + rate(urlshortener_cache_requests_total{result=\"miss\"}[5m])) * 100",
          "legendFormat": "hit ratio",
          "refId": "A"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "title": "Cache Hit vs Miss (req/s)",
      "description": "Cache lookup rate broken down by result.\n\nThe green area (hits) should dominate the red area (misses). Right after a restart, you'll see all misses until the cache warms up. This is normal.",
      "type": "timeseries",
      "gridPos": {
        "h": 8,
        "w": 10,
        "x": 6,
        "y": 18
      },
      "id": 7,
      "datasource": {
        "type": "prometheus",
        "uid": "PBFA97CFB590B2093"
      },
      "fieldConfig": {
        "defaults": {
          "custom": {
            "axisBorderShow": false,
            "drawStyle": "line",
            "fillOpacity": 40,
            "lineInterpolation": "smooth",
            "lineWidth": 2,
            "stacking": {
              "group": "A",
              "mode": "normal"
            }
          },
          "unit": "reqps"
        },
        "overrides": [
          {
            "matcher": {
              "id": "byName",
              "options": "hit"
            },
            "properties": [
              {
                "id": "color",
                "value": {
                  "fixedColor": "green",
                  "mode": "fixed"
                }
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "matcher": {
              "id": "byName",
              "options": "miss"
            },
            "properties": [
              {
                "id": "color",
                "value": {
                  "fixedColor": "red",
                  "mode": "fixed"
                }
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      },
      "options": {
        "legend": {
          "calcs": [
            "mean",
            "lastNotNull"
          ],
          "displayMode": "table",
          "placement": "bottom"
        },
        "tooltip": {
          "mode": "multi",
          "sort": "desc"
        }
      },
      "targets": [
        {
          "expr": "rate(urlshortener_cache_requests_total{result=\"hit\"}[5m])",
          "legendFormat": "hit",
          "refId": "A"
        },
        {
          "expr": "rate(urlshortener_cache_requests_total{result=\"miss\"}[5m])",
          "legendFormat": "miss",
          "refId": "B"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "title": "Cache Errors",
      "description": "Redis operation failures per second.\n\nThis should always be 0. Any value > 0 means Redis is having issues (connection refused, timeout, OOM). Even a brief spike deserves investigation because during that period, ALL requests fall through to the database.",
      "type": "stat",
      "gridPos": {
        "h": 8,
        "w": 8,
        "x": 16,
        "y": 18
      },
      "id": 8,
      "datasource": {
        "type": "prometheus",
        "uid": "PBFA97CFB590B2093"
      },
      "fieldConfig": {
        "defaults": {
          "color": {
            "mode": "thresholds"
          },
          "thresholds": {
            "mode": "absolute",
            "steps": [
              {
                "color": "green",
                "value": null
              },
              {
                "color": "red",
