    {
      "title": "Pipeline Health",
      "description": "Batch operations: flushes and errors per second.\n\nFlushes should be steady. Errors should be 0.\n\nAverage batch size = inserted_rate / flush_rate.\nIf batch size is consistently small (< 10), the flush interval is firing before batches fill up (low traffic, normal). If batch size equals BatchSize config (100), workers are at capacity.",
